Interview with Terrox (ex-Spaceballs)
µJEµF1µC1
µI0219
Until the present day for me the once leading diskmag of the Amiga demoscene, the king of its genre, was (and still is) with no doubt: RAW !! (= R.evolutionary A.rticle W.ork)

And not only for me, it still finds its place into the recent charts, nine years after it has been released for the LAST time! It`s been a true masterpiece in diskmag art, if there`s something you could call it that way. Sceners at the beginning or middle of the 90s could either love or hate it. No way possible inbetween. There were the fraction of lamers, like me. We adored this mag because of its fantastic graphics, the most impressive startpictures have been painted by Fairfax of Andromeda! For its good music and especially for the entertainment and mass of informations you could expect content wise.

The other fraction were those, who`ve been heavily insulted by Lord Helmets` articles. People like Chaos of Sanity (now Farbrausch) or Hydra, the leader of Andromeda. Lord Helmet didn`t spare anybody, no matter if he was a person with a good reputation, somebody with a big power or not. He wrote what came into his mind, he wrote what he was convinced of. No, risk - no fun!?

Lord Helmet invented the ruthless, aggressive writing style he became famous for. He influenced all editors that began writing after him. RAW was a sort of scenish "Bild-Zeitung". All the scandals, all the disclosing articles were published there.

The creme de la creme of the writing guild gathered around him. They knew which potential RAW offered and wanted to see their articles and their names inside this publication.

So, why not making an interview with this shy norwegian figure, called Boerge Brunes aka Lord Helmet? No, I prefer doing one with a person, who was also very important for the success of this project, but he mostly acted in the background. For most of you Terrox isn`t known at all. "Terrox, who`s Terrox???", you might ask.

Come with me, jump into the time machine and let`s go back to the age, when the Scene was still ROCKING!


µC2Hi Terrox, please introduce yourself to the readers!

µC3Hello Jurassic Pack readers!

I`m most known in the Scene as Terrox. My real name is Kent-Rune K. Saetrum and I am 29 years old. I live in Oslo in Norway, where I run my own businesses.

Back in 1987 I bought my first Amiga 500, and it was really expensive at that time. For two or three years I was mostly gaming, until I discovered the world of the Amiga Scene in 1990. Later I bought an Amiga 600, 1200 and at last the Amiga 4000 dream computer.
Then I started using modem and traded games, demos, software, modules and graphics as an independent guy. I also sent like five parcels every day with floppy disks to Sceners all around Europe. Remember, this was before internet was common, and BBS owners were like rich popstars to us snail-mail swappers.

I got in touch with lots of nice people. Those I manage to remember after many years outside the Scene are so far:

Lord Helmet/RAW, Astro/RAW, Lars Haugseth (RAW coder), Cesium/Session, Mr.Hyde/Andromeda, Travolta/Spaceballs, Damion/Artwork, Ghandy, Sixpack, Dr.Awesome, Dreamer/Nah Color, Virgill, E-Moon/TBL, Chaos/Sanity, Gargoyle/Polka Brothers, Jester/Sanity, Jogeir/Noiseless, Lizardking, Macno, Rokdazone, Zerox/Gods and lots of forgotten names.

